Digiworld : distributes supplements with profit margin over 60%



































0






05/25/2017 | 09:16am CEST 


Send by mail :
Last Name :
Name :
From* :
To* :
(You can enter multiple email addresses separated by commas)
Message :
*Required fields







AGM 2017: Digiworld expands its business to a new sector, which has profit margin over 60%



        At the Annual General Meeting of Shareholders on 28 April 2017, Digiworld Corporation (DGW) officially announced its industry expansion distributing segment in healthcare and home-careproducts. According to the plan, the company will launch its first healthcare product in 2017. It is estimated that this segment has a profit margin over 60%, contributing 80 billion VND revenue in 2017 and is expected to grow 100% / year, targeted to reach 600 billion VND in revenue in 2020.
      

        Entering into the new industry, DGW aims to  make full use of its  core competencies - as a professional provider of Market Expansion Service (MES) in Vietnam. Since  MES is not just for ICT, it is also indispensable need of every industry. Especially, with brand-new or already-on-shelfe products of good quality  but poor marketing, weak sales and lack of distribution system, MES is an urgent need for their development.
      

        In response to the question of whetherDGW is gradually leaving its traditional business (ICT), Mr. Doan Hong Viet, DGW's Chairman cum  General Director confirmed that DGW does not abandon ICT but rather develop new ones to take advantage of its core competencies.
      

        Healthcare product group, which DGW is targeting, includes healthy supplements for men, women,children, beauty care and , heart-supporting products etc.  DGW's priority in choosing partners who have good products (accredited by doctors), has just joined the market or brand image hasn't been built well, develop in accordance with their potential yet.
      

        Expected in the beginning of 3rd quarter of 2017, supplement food is the first product will be officially launched to the market through network of pharmacies in Vietnam. Also with this product, DGW will be a 'pioneer' to bring customer service when purchasing supplements or pharmaceuticals to Vietnamese consumers, DWG will collaborate with the  specialist doctors to ensure the quality as well as safety of the products, build a qualified and skilled team of consultants. Therefore, if successful, the company will continue to deploy related products.
      

        Towards the middle of 2019, DGW targets to  cover 20,000 pharmacies. There are roughly 40.000 pharmacies nationwide currently. As known, supplement food is an segment that  has high profit margin, about 60-65% (from  production line to consumer approach).
      



Digiworld Corp. published this content on 25 May 2017 and is solely responsible for the information contained herein. Distributed by Public, unedited and unaltered, on  25 May 2017 07:15:18 UTC.
          


